modules.description: Provides methods to append and remove elements from both ends of a doubly linked list in constant time. Operates on elements stored in a structured, mutable list format. Used for efficient task scheduling and queue management in event-driven systems.

This module offers bidirectional manipulation of mutable double-linked lists, enabling efficient element insertion, deletion, and iteration from both ends, along with folding operations across nodes. It includes predicate-based search capabilities for locating nodes in either direction, returning results via options or exceptions, suitable for dynamic data management scenarios like event queues or real-time processing pipelines. The operations support fine-grained node-level modifications and traversal, ideal for applications requiring frequent structural updates and conditional element access.
